  "texts": [
    "It describes the creation of two datasets: the Economic Abstracts (EA) dataset for model pre-training and the Oil Markets (OM) dataset for finetuning.",
    "The chapter also elaborates on the application used to measure each technique such as, zero-shot learning, fine-tuning, pre-training, and adapter training techniques.",
    "It will emphase the rationale behind the selection of specific LLMs and the implementation of prompt engineering.After, in the fourth chapter will present the research's findings, comparing the performance of different language models in sentiment analysis for the oil commodity market.",
    "The analysis reveals the superior performance of LLMs, particularly when optimized through prompt engineering techniques.",
    "The chapter also highlights the limitations of smaller language models when dealing with small labeled datasets like OM and the importance of few-shot learning as an efficient solution for sentiment analysis in this context."
